headline.main: FINSCHHAFEN FOE THRASHING IN NET; Fails in Savage Counter-Blows to Break Allied Grip on New Guinea Base

lead_paragraph: ALLIED HEADQUARTERS IN SOUTHWEST PACIFIC, Friday, Oct. 1 (AP) -- Australian jungle troops are closing in on the last Japanese positions at Finschhafen, New Guinea, after having hurled back three savage Japanese counter-attacks on Tuesday that sought to break the strangle-hold.
